Paper: 12063067
Title: Comment on "Can we measure structures to a precision better than the  Planck length?"[arXiv:1205.3636], by Sabine Hossenfelder
Authors: Sergio Doplicher and Gherardo Piacitelli and Luca Tomassini and Stefano Viaggiu
Abstract: First principles do imply a non-zero minimal distance between events in spacetime, but no positive lower bound to the precision of the measurement of a single coordinate.
